<para id="fs-id1167063424458"><link target-id="Figure_18_01_Conservati"/> shows two spheres that initially have +4 C and +8 C of charge. After an interaction (which could simply be that they touch each other), the blue sphere has +10 C of charge, and the red sphere has an unknown quantity of charge. Use the law of conservation of charge to find the final charge on the red sphere.</para><note id="eip-id1167061289420">
<label/><title>Strategy</title>
<para id="fs-id1167066866290">The net initial charge of the system is  <m:math>
