<para id="fs-id1164565977644">A solid cube carries a charge of +25<emphasis effect="italics">e</emphasis>. You measure the charge on each face of the cube and find that each face carries +3<emphasis effect="italics">e</emphasis> of charge. Is the cube made of conducting or insulating material? Explain.</para>
